scheduler.db.coursedb
Class Course

java.lang.Object
  scheduler.db.coursedb.Course
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Course>
public class Course
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Course>

This class will contain the information necessary to represent a course available to the instructor, such as its name and required equipment.

Author:
Cedric Wienold

Course

public Course(Course c)
Returns a new course, whose fields are the same as the supplied course. In particular, "the same" means the "have the same reference" as. As of right now (15nov10), this makes a shallow copy of the object, though all non-object fields will, of course, be copied. Note: This particular constructor if pivotal to passing a copy of all to the schedule generator. In this way, the algorithm can do whatever it likes to the Courses w/o fear of altering the originals.

Parameters:
c - Course to copy

hasLab

public boolean hasLab()
Throws an UnsupportedOperationException object when called. Children classes must extend this method. It is only provided so that a call to [some Course object].hasLab() can work, when the [some Course object] is some other child class (such as a Lecture).

hoursDivideIntoDays

public boolean hoursDivideIntoDays(int numOfDays)
Determines whether a given number of days are suitable for teaching this course over. In particular, this means that the hours/week this course is taught divide evenly among the given number of days, and in such as manner that the Course will be taught at least one hour every day.

Parameters:
numOfDays - The number of days the class is to be taught.
Returns:
((((this.hoursPerWeek * 2) % numOfDays) == 0) && (this.hoursPerWeek * 2) / numOfDays) > 1));
